# Production runtime = lean base + the DP-238 voice/STT stack.
# Compiled into requirements-voice.txt via pip-compile; the Dockerfile installs
# requirements-voice.txt for production builds.
#
# DP-250: split out from requirements.in so CI (requirements-dev.txt) can stay
# lean. These deps drag in heavy ML wheels (numba/llvmlite/onnxruntime/
# scikit-learn/scipy/librosa/huggingface-hub) that are large and lag new Python
# releases — undesirable for the CI install path, required for prod voice.
#
# Lazy-imported only when VOICE_ENABLED. Needs libopus + ffmpeg in the container
# image (see Dockerfile). Moonshine's onnx backend is a SEPARATE package
# `useful-moonshine-onnx` (import `moonshine_onnx`) — CPU-only, no torch; there
# is no `[onnx]` extra on the base `useful-moonshine` package.
-r requirements.in

discord-ext-voice-recv  # voice receive (stock discord.py only sends)
useful-moonshine-onnx  # STT (import name: moonshine_onnx); onnx pkg = CPU, no torch
# pynacl: transitive via discord.py[voice]. Dependabot medium CVE wants >=1.6.2
# (libsodium incomplete-disallowed-inputs), but discord.py 2.7.1 (latest) caps
# PyNaCl<1.6 -> can't bump until discord.py relaxes the pin. Blocked upstream. DP-251.
